    q: "How old is too old for Hobart repair?",
    a: "Age isn't the trigger — parts availability is. ITW's parts chain on Hobart commercial dishwashers is strong for 20-year-old units because ITW deliberately keeps parts in production long after a model line is superseded. Our honest cutoff is usually 25+ years, and even then, it's usually a specific electronic control board or obsolete proprietary part that pushes us toward replace-not-repair. AM16 units from the early 2000s still have parts flowing. LXe undercounters from the mid-2000s still have parts. We've serviced 22-year-old Hobarts in LA where every common part was available. The question isn't 'how old,' it's 'which specific part needs replacing.'"
