  },
  {
    q: "Do you service used Hobart units bought from restaurant liquidations?",
    a: "Yes — this is a common LA scenario. The restaurant liquidation pipeline (restaurantequipment.bid, used-equipment brokers) moves a lot of Hobart inventory every time an operator closes. The challenge with a used Hobart is not knowing the service history — was the unit run hard in a 400-cover-a-night chain, or light-duty in a neighborhood spot, and what did the previous operator skip on preventive maintenance? We offer a pre-purchase inspection service for buyers negotiating used Hobart deals — a paid $120 diagnostic visit where we pull the front panel, test wash and rinse pressures, inspect the tank and wash-arm condition, verify booster operation, and give a written condition report. Protects against walking into a $2,500 hidden-repair scenario."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Hobart commercial dishwasher repair cost in LA?",
    a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Typical Hobart service ranges across LA: rinse arm spray bearing $180–$320, door gasket $180–$320, fill solenoid $200–$340, booster heater contactor $220–$360, chemical dispenser solenoid $220–$380, door switch $160–$240, drain pump $280–$440, wash pump seal kit $300–$480, booster element $320–$540, wash pump replacement $500–$820, control board $700–$1,400, conveyor drive motor (CL line) $550–$950, compressor or tank heater (older units) $800–$1,500. Most Hobart calls land $350–$750 parts-and-labor; CL rack-conveyor jobs $650–$1,200. Hobart Corp direct typically lists callout alone at $300–$400 before any repair."
  }
