      <h2>Hobart — America's #1 commercial dishwasher, and where an independent tech fits</h2>
      <p>
        Hobart Corporation is the oldest and largest commercial dishwasher brand in the United States. The company
        traces to 1897 Troy, Ohio, became part of Dart &amp; Kraft in 1981, Premark International in 1986, and has
        been part of the ITW Food Equipment Group since 1999. Hobart is the definitional American commercial
        foodservice-equipment brand — the AM16 is to commercial kitchens what the Kenworth is to long-haul trucking.
      </p>
      <p>
        Hobart Corporation also runs its own direct service network — 125 service locations across the US, 1,500
        technicians, their own LA office. For an LA operator, that's a real service infrastructure. The question
        we answer with this page isn't "who makes Hobart dishwashers" — it's "when do you call Hobart Corp direct
        versus an independent tech?" The honest answer is: Hobart Corp for warranty work, new-install commissioning,
        and large contract accounts; independent for out-of-warranty repairs, emergency after-hours, weekends, and
        situations where the corporate dispatch window is 24–48 hours and your kitchen can't wait that long.
      </p>
      <p>
        The other real gap is pricing. Hobart Corp direct typically lists a $300–$400 callout charge before any
        repair, plus parts, plus labor. We run $120 diagnostic waived with repair. For a door-gasket replacement,
        that alone is the difference between a $250 invoice and a $550 invoice. We don't say anything bad about
        Hobart Corp's service quality — their techs are good. We say that for the out-of-warranty segment of the
        market, an independent alternative with stocked parts and honest pricing is the sensible choice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

